adjectives.description: unseamanlike (comparative more unseamanlike, superlative most unseamanlike)

entries.meaning: Not characteristic of or befitting a seaman.
examples: On behalf of the Dundee, it was deposed, that the loss of the Princess Charlotte was purely accidental, or if attributable to any mismanagement, attributable only to the unseamanlike conduct of the Princess Charlotte's own people […]
